ove background\nvalues. These spikes are driven by spikes in the non-force free component of\nthe current density. The times of these spikes are plausibly correlated with\ntimes of subsequent M or X flares a few hours to a few days later. The spikes\noccur on granulation scales, and may be signatures of heating in horizontal\ncurrent sheets. It is also found that the times of relatively large values of\nthe rate of change of the NLR unsigned magnetic flux are also plausibly\ncorrelated with the times of subsequent M and X flares, and spikes in $Q_i$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 3 Mar 2020 22:44:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 27 Apr 2020 19:15:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-29"}
