iod is also highly variable with a peak of $\\sim$ 30$\\%$ one day after the\n$\\gamma$-ray flare. Near simultaneous $\\gamma$-ray flux points show a linear\nanti-correlation with the degree of polarization during the period of\n$\\gamma$-ray flare. The significant drop in the degree of linear polarization\nsuggests a sudden increase in the tangled magnetic field strength in the\nemission region.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 Mar 2020 11:03:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-05"}
