l perturbers constitute an important tool in studies of cometary\ndynamics. The usage of our data significantly changes results of the past and\nfuture comet motion analysis. We point out a puzzling object in our list, star\nALS 9243. The Gaia DR2 astrometry suggests a very close encounter of this star\nwith the Sun however, its astrophysical parameters result in a completely\ndifferent current distance of ALS 9243 and its large mass.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 Mar 2020 13:24:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 27 Apr 2020 10:03:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-31"}
